Sentencas: In this paper, the nonmetallic Si4+-doped modified lanthanum aluminate (LaAlO3) solid electrolyte for the first time, which has particular scientific significance, and LaAl1-xSixO3-6 material was successfully prepared by the sol-gel method.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Si-doped LaAlO3 solid electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: LaAl1-xSixO3-6 is a ceramic material sintered at 1100 degrees C for 2 h in an air atmosphere.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Si-doped LaAlO3 solid electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The surface microstructure and electrochemical properties of the samples were tested by multiple characterization methods.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Si-doped LaAlO3 solid electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The results show that the LaAl1-xSixO3-6 has good sintering activity, high crystallinity, and a grain radius of approximately 25 nm.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Si-doped LaAlO3 solid electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, the ionic conductivity is above 1.05E-04 Smiddotcm(-1) and the activation energy is lower than 1.19 eV.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of Si-doped LaAlO3 solid electrolyte for IT-SOFCs
